First substitute \(x=5i\) into  
\[y=\frac{x+1}{2-x}=\frac{5i+1}{2-5i}.\]  
Multiply top and bottom by the conjugate of the denominator, \(2+5i\):  
\[
y=\frac{(1+5i)(2+5i)}{(2-5i)(2+5i)}
=\frac{2+5i+10i+25i^2}{4+25}
=\frac{2+15i-25}{29}
=\frac{-23+15i}{29}
=-\frac{23}{29}+\frac{15}{29}i.
\]

To simplify \((6+4i)/i\), multiply numerator and denominator by \(-i\) (since \(i\cdot(-i)=1\)):

\[
\frac{6+4i}{i}
\;=\;\frac{(6+4i)\,(-i)}{i\,(-i)}
\;=\;\frac{-6i -4i^2}{-i^2}
\;=\;\frac{-6i -4(-1)}{-(-1)}
\;=\;\frac{-6i +4}{1}
\;=\;4 - 6i.
\]

Multiply numerator and denominator by the conjugate of the denominator:

\[
\frac{3+4i}{2 - i}\;\times\;\frac{2 + i}{2 + i}
=\frac{(3+4i)(2+i)}{(2-i)(2+i)}
=\frac{6+3i+8i+4i^2}{4 - i^2}
=\frac{6+11i-4}{4-(-1)}
=\frac{2+11i}{5}
=\frac{2}{5}+\frac{11}{5}i.
\]
